		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Deconstructing the Balrog - A Preliminary Look<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.47)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2214'>Michael "mc9457" Carr</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2214&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 16, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> NOTE:  This was posted earlier today on the Decipher List Serve by me.  However, I made one tiny error in my initial analysis in regards to the bridge.  Here is an updated analysis with consideration of the bridge AND consideration of the beast combo that has everyone upset.<br />
<br />
So, now we finally see the mighty Balrog - the scourge of the underworld. How deadly is he? Let&#39;s take a look.<br />
<br />
He is Moria - but fortunately not an Orc.<br />
<br />
He is limited to underground sites - which are sites 4 & 5.<br />
<br />
He removes the archery phase.<br />
<br />
He is fierce - only the second Moria to have that ability.<br />
<br />
He is damage +1 - unless you are using adders or double teaming, again only the second Moria to have that abiltiy.<br />
<br />
He discards all other minions. In multiplayer this is huge (think of the mind games that will be played at site 5 with this guy out).<br />
<br />
He is a power 17 - a mere 2 more then the Cave Troll.<br />
<br />
He costs 12 to get onto the table - more then any other minion to date.<br />
<br />
He has a health of 5 - again the highest on a Minion to date.<br />
<br />
Now, banning all other potential cards to come out, and taking into consideration the Uruk X (where X=any Uruk who can Exert) /Sauramon’s Snows/Balrog beats combo lets take a look at his inherent weaknesses.<br />
<br />
First, for those who have not heard of this combo hear it is:<br />
<br />
Uruk X, then play Sauramon’s Snows.  Then play Balrog and your opponent can play no Skirmish stuff.<br />
<br />
Now on with the deconstruction.<br />
<br />
Twilight Cost of 12:<br />
<br />
This is a problem. Why? Take a look at your average hobbit deck. These decks make use of A Talent For Not Being Seen, which reduces the twighlight of a site by 2 for 4 hobbits, 1 for 2 hobbits. Lets take the extreme of 4 hobbits. Site 4 will net Shadow a total pool of 5 twilight. So what you say? Well, at sites 1-3, he is a waste of a card in hand, and site 4 is the first site he can be played at.  Without 12 twilight to pay for him…well your ship is sunk.  You suddenly have this card in hand that is completely and thoroughly useless until site 5 when you can finally play him.  Now, if you want to pull the combo off, you are going to need at least 2 for Snows, 6 for Balrog, and 2 for Uruk Savage (cheapest deploy, highest health).  That means you need 10 twilight.  Versus this hobbit deck you would receive 4 for the fellowship and 4 for the site for a total of 8.  That means no Snows for you.  No Snows = Hobbit runs away from two battles (two Hobbit Stealths) and Balrog dies when you move on.  Add the upcoming Bill the Pony from the league set (spoiler is somewhere on www.theonering.net) and you have even less to use. <br />
<br />
Discarded if Not Underground:<br />
<br />
So this minion is useful at two sites, and one of those isn&#39;t even a guarantee. Site 4 and 5 are the only two sites (to date) that are underground. Site 4 can easily be Cadaharas (sp?) through the proper manipulations (Thror&#39;s Map, Pathfinder, Nazgul who can replace sites).<br />
<br />
Power 17:<br />
<br />
Yes, this will easily double most characters power.  But will it triple? Come on. You play the right cards, and you need darn near 30 to overwhelm most characters. And most of these aren&#39;t even Skirmish actions! There and Back Again + Merry + Hobbit Sword = Power 9 hobbit. Doesn&#39;t even double his power.<br />
<br />
Damage +1:<br />
<br />
So you inflict two wounds on two characters before site 6 - a sanctuary. Great. Unless Black Breath or You Bring Great Evil is on one of these two, forget the damage you just inflicted.<br />
<br />
Discard all other minions:<br />
<br />
The best part of the Cave Troll is not in his power, but in the fact that he can have his friends around to overwhelm poor Frodo. Example: For 12 Twilight you can play the Balrog OR you can play 4 Goblin Runners, Cave Troll, 4 Moria Scouts minimum. 9 characters versus 1. Which would you rather face? Personally, I will take the Balrog any day. Unless your fellowship is actually up to 9 or has 4 people who are defender +1, your poor little Frodo is so dead.<br />
<br />
Now with all that said, there are plenty of benefits for playing the Balrog: He is fierce, his health - which matters little with his power, the lack of Archery phase, and the fact he can played from the draw deck.<br />
<br />
So there is my brief analysis of this super Moria character. Yes he is good, but I would not go building a deck around him. He is great against the Mirror, fast moving decks, and Archery decks. Will you face him in every deck? Probably. But if you do, just be glad that you will not have to face anyone else at site 5. Remember, the alternative is the Cave Troll and his friends.... <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=3147&view=1&PHPSESSID=78d9e376d7e05238a2339aec8e27f4f4'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=78d9e376d7e05238a2339aec8e27f4f4'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=78d9e376d7e05238a2339aec8e27f4f4'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
